            "title": "Node Options For NodeJS",
            "date_published": "2021-11-17T09:00:00.000Z",
            "content_html": "<h1 id=\"nodejs-options-node_options\"><a class=\"markdownIt-Anchor\" href=\"#nodejs-options-node_options\"></a> NODEJS OPTIONS [ NODE_OPTIONS ]</h1>\n<p>Node.js accompanies an assortment of CLI choices. These choices uncover worked in investigating, different ways of executing scripts, and other accommodating runtime choices.</p>\n<p>To see this documentation as a manual page in a terminal, run ‘man hub’. <a href=\"https://nodejs.org/api/cli.html\">Read more</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"how-to-setup-multiple-options-on-github-workflow\"><a class=\"markdownIt-Anchor\" href=\"#how-to-setup-multiple-options-on-github-workflow\"></a> How to setup multiple options on GitHub Workflow</h2>\n<figure class=\"highlight yaml\"><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br><span class=\"line\">2</span><br><span class=\"line\">3</span><br><span class=\"line\">4</span><br><span class=\"line\">5</span><br><span class=\"line\">6</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"attr\">jobs:</span></span><br><span class=\"line\">  <span class=\"attr\">build:</span></span><br><span class=\"line\">    <span class=\"attr\">name:</span> <span class=\"string\">Build</span> <span class=\"string\">www.webmanajemen.com</span></span><br><span class=\"line\">    <span class=\"attr\">runs-on:</span> <span class=\"string\">ubuntu-latest</span></span><br><span class=\"line\">    <span class=\"attr\">env:</span></span><br><span class=\"line\">      <span class=\"attr\">NODE_OPTIONS:</span> <span class=\"string\">&quot;--experimental-vm-modules --max_old_space_size=8192&quot;</span></span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>\n<h2 id=\"how-to-performance-run-nodejs-on-low-devices\"><a class=\"markdownIt-Anchor\" href=\"#how-to-performance-run-nodejs-on-low-devices\"></a> How to performance run nodejs on low devices</h2>\n<p>The recommended amounts for a “low memory device”.</p>\n<p>for 32-bit and/or Android are:</p>\n<figure class=\"highlight shell\"><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\">node --max-executable-size=96 --max-old-space-size=128 --max-semi-space-size=1 app.js</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>\n<p>for 64-bit non-android are:</p>\n<figure class=\"highlight shell\"><table><tr><td class=\"gutter\"><pre><span class=\"line\">1</span><br></pre></td><td class=\"code\"><pre><span class=\"line\">node --max-executable-size=192 --max-old-space-size=256 --max-semi-space-size=2 app.js</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>\n<p>These above codes would limit the heap totals to 225mb and 450mb respectively. It doesn’t include memory usage outside JS. For instance buffers are allocated as “c memory” , not in the JavaScript heap.</p>\n<h3 id=\"flags\"><a class=\"markdownIt-Anchor\" href=\"#flags\"></a> Flags</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><code>--max-executable-size</code> the maximum size of heap reserved for executable code (the native code result of just-in-time compiled JavaScript).</li>\n<li><code>--max-old-space-size</code> the maximum size of heap reserved for long term objects</li>\n<li><code>--max-semi-space-size</code> the maximum size of heap reserved for short term objects</li>\n</ul>\n",
            "tags": [
                "JS",
